---
import ContainerLayout from "../../layouts/ContainerLayout.astro";
import ContentSection from "../../components/ContentSection.astro";
import ProjectList from "../../components/ProjectList.astro";
import { i18n } from "../../i18n";
import projectsData from "../../content/work/projects.json";
import productishCover from "../../assets/legacy/productish.jpg";

const lang = "en";
const t = i18n[lang];

const openSource = projectsData.openSource;
const projects = projectsData.all;
---

<ContainerLayout
  title={`${t.work.title} · ${t.siteTitle}`}
  description={t.siteDescription}
  lang={lang}
  padTop
  padBottom
>
  <section class="page">
    <h1>{t.work.title}</h1>
    <p class="lead">Build great digital products efficiently</p>
    <p>
      The beauty of digital product development is: "Anything is possible, it is
      just a matter of time and money." That is also its curse. It enables both
      insufficiently small and overwhelmingly complex solutions.
    </p>
    <p>
      That is why I start with business and customer needs and then recommend the
      most efficient technical solution, often by selecting strong third-party tools.
    </p>

    <ContentSection title="Publications">
      <p>A few publications where I tried to pass on what I learned.</p>
      <ul class="publications">
        <li>
          <img src="/images/legacy/publications/digitales-produktmanagement.jpg" alt="Cover of Digitales Produktmanagement" loading="lazy" />
          <div>
            <a href="https://www.springer.com/de/book/9783658306281#aboutAuthors" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Digitales Produktmanagement</a>
            <p class="subtitle">Methods - Tools - Practical Examples</p>
            <p>
              In this German book on digital product management, I contributed a chapter on efficiently building and delivering products.
            </p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li>
          <img src="/images/legacy/publications/programmierbar-cto-special-18.jpg" alt="Artwork of programmier.bar CTO-SPECIAL #18" loading="lazy" />
          <div>
            <a href="https://www.programmier.bar/podcast/cto-special-18-tim-adler-von-chefkoch" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">programmier.bar</a>
            <p class="subtitle">CTO-SPECIAL #18</p>
            <p>
              In this episode I talked, still as CTO of Chefkoch, about my CV and why I regularly switch between hands-on development and management.
            </p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li>
          <img src={productishCover.src} width={productishCover.width} height={productishCover.height} alt="Cover image of the Productish podcast" loading="lazy" />
          <div>
            <p>Productish Podcast</p>
            <p class="subtitle">A podcast on conflicts and challenges in digital product management</p>
            <p>
              Together with my colleague and friend Tim Herbig, I co-hosted around 15 episodes discussing recurring product management problems and conflicts.
            </p>
          </div>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </ContentSection>

    <ContentSection title="Open Source">
      <p>
        I still contribute to open source too rarely, but here are projects I built or contributed to.
      </p>
      <ProjectList lang={lang} items={openSource} />
    </ContentSection>

    <ContentSection title="Projects">
      <p>
        In the following projects, I helped build something new, from relaunches to fresh product launches.
      </p>
      <ProjectList lang={lang} items={projects} />
    </ContentSection>
  </section>
</ContainerLayout>

<style>
  .page {
    display: grid;
    gap: var(--space-2xl);
    max-width: 76ch;
    margin-inline: auto;
  }

  h1 {
    margin: 0;
  }

  .kicker {
    margin: 0;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--gray-10);
    font-size: var(--step--1);
  }

  .lead {
    font-size: var(--step-3);
    line-height: var(--line-height-tight);
    max-width: 24ch;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .page > p:not(.kicker):not(.lead) {
    margin: 0;
    max-width: 66ch;
    line-height: var(--line-height-snug);
  }

  .page :global(.content-section) {
    border-top: 1px solid var(--gray-5);
    padding-top: var(--space-xl);
  }

  .page :global(.content-section h2) {
    font-size: var(--step-2);
  }

  .publications {
    list-style: none;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    display: grid;
    gap: var(--space-m);
  }

  .publications li {
    display: grid;
    gap: var(--space-m);
    align-items: start;
    padding: 0 0 var(--space-m);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--gray-5);

    @media (width >= 760px) {
      grid-template-columns: 8rem 1fr;
      column-gap: var(--space-l);
    }
  }

  .publications li:last-child {
    border-bottom: 0;
    padding-bottom: 0;
  }

  .publications p {
    margin: 0;
  }

  .publications a {
    font-weight: var(--font-weight-medium);
  }

  .publications img {
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
    border-radius: var(--radius-s);
    object-fit: cover;
  }

  .page :global(.project-list) {
    gap: var(--space-m);
  }

  .page :global(.project-list > li) {
    padding: 0 0 var(--space-m);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--gray-5);
  }

  .page :global(.project-list > li:last-child) {
    border-bottom: 0;
    padding-bottom: 0;
  }

  .page :global(.project-list article) {
    display: grid;
    gap: var(--space-xs);
  }

  .page :global(.project-list h3) {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: var(--step-1);
    line-height: var(--line-height-tight);
  }

  .subtitle {
    margin: 0;
    font-weight: var(--font-weight-medium);
    color: var(--gray-11);
  }
</style>
